analysis: The documents in this cluster primarily concern the delegation of authority and responsibilities within the Executive Branch, particularly focusing on national security, economic sanctions, and emergency preparedness. They involve amendments to existing executive orders to reflect changes in agency responsibilities, address threats from foreign adversaries, and ensure the protection of classified information. The documents also cover aspects of manpower utilization during wartime and occupational safety and health programs for federal employees.
title: Executive Branch Authority and National Security Directives
